{
  "_readme": [
    "THE project registry (design doc \u00a73.5) \u2014 known-mod-repos.json's v2 successor,",
    "consolidated 2026-07-23 (Phase 4). Two jobs, one file: (a) project discovery",
    "for the multi-project framework, and (b) the reviewed AUTO-CLONE ALLOWLIST the",
    "worker consults \u2014 a repo absent here is never cloned by name, and that refusal",
    "is a safety property (REMOTE-TESTING.md 'No auto-clone'), not a bug.",
    "PROJECT-SESSION-WRITABLE (baton-exempt): onboarding a project, or adding a mod",
    "repo you have started work on, never requires the design master \u2014 add the entry,",
    "commit + push, and every worker picks it up on its next ff-pull.",
    "No secrets, no machine paths (those live in machine-local *.local sidecars",
    "mapping project_id -> clone path/creds). Readers accept the legacy flat shape",
    "too (profile_runtime._registry_corresponds), so old job files still validate.",
    "NOTE: the framework peer's own clone URL is NOT read from here \u2014 it is a",
    "git-reviewed constant in the harness's _agentops_bootstrap.py, because this",
    "file lives inside the repo that bootstrap has to clone."
  ],
